Singer, Ikuforiji Olaitan Abdulrahman aka Oxlade has opened up on his mental health. The 24-year old entertainer, who took a brief break from the music scene after a s3x tape scandal, revealed that he is happy at the moment.   How a record label boss almost ruined my career, life, by…     Two kids of ex-girlfriend not mine, says OAP Fada Kane     R. Kelly thrills inmate’s daughter via phone call in…   In an interview with Beat FM, the “Ojuju” crooner, who recently bagged an international deal with Epic Records, an American record label owned by Sony Entertainment followed with a song titled ‘Want You’ said he in a place doing what he loves while ignoring distractions. “Honestly! Right now, I am at a place where I love doing what I’m doing and I don’t even want to pay attention to anything else” Oxlade said. While evading the question that attempted to confirm his true mental state, Oxlade said: I’m happy, that’s all that matters.”